{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Integral.html#integral_isDimensionallyCorrect\"><span class=\"name\">integral_isDimensionallyCorrect</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#HasDim\">HasDim</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Group/Arithmetic.html#MeasurableConstSMul\">MeasurableConstSMul</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#HasDim\">HasDim</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Dimension.html#Dimension\">Dimension</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#IsDimensionallyCorrect\">IsDimensionallyCorrect</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#DimSet\">DimSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#DimSet\">DimSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> → <span class=\"fn\">G</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#dim\">dim</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inv.inv\">⁻¹</a>))</span></span>) =&gt;\n  <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The statement that for a measure `μ` of dimension `d`, and a function\n  `f : M → G` of dimension `(CarriesDimension.d G * d⁻¹)` (where `CarriesDimension.d G`\n  is the dimension associated with terms of type `G`), then\n  `∫ x, f x ∂μ `\n  has the correct dimension, namely `CarriesDimension.d G`.\n\n  In other words, the function:\n```\nfun (μ : DimSet (MeasureTheory.Measure M) d)\n    (f : DimSet (M → G) (CarriesDimension.d G * d⁻¹)) ↦ ∫ x, f.1 x ∂μ.1\n```\n  is dimensionally correct. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Units/Integral.html#integral_isDimensionallyCorrect","kind":"theorem","line":55,"name":"integral_isDimensionallyCorrect","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L55-L109"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Integral.html#scaleUnit_measure\"><span class=\"name\">scaleUnit_measure</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#HasDim\">HasDim</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Group/Arithmetic.html#MeasurableConstSMul\">MeasurableConstSMul</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">u1 </span><span class=\"fn\">u2</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#UnitChoices\">UnitChoices</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#UnitDependent.scaleUnit\">UnitDependent.scaleUnit</a> <span class=\"fn\">u1</span> <span class=\"fn\">u2</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Map.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.map\">MeasureTheory.Measure.map</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#UnitDependent.scaleUnit\">UnitDependent.scaleUnit</a> <span class=\"fn\">u1</span> <span class=\"fn\">u2</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Units/Integral.html#scaleUnit_measure","kind":"theorem","line":52,"name":"scaleUnit_measure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L52-L53"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Integral.html#instMulUnitDependentMeasureOfHasDimOfMeasurableConstSMulReal\"><span class=\"name\">instMulUnitDependentMeasureOfHasDimOfMeasurableConstSMulReal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/Basic.html#HasDim\">HasDim</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Group/Arithmetic.html#MeasurableConstSMul\">MeasurableConstSMul</a